## 4. Implemented Optimizations

### High-Stability Optimizations
1.  **Thread Decoupling (Non-Blocking Capture)**: Split capture from processing. Capture thread is now "Ultra-Light", preventing `libcamerasrc` from ever timing out due to slow downstream tasks.
2.  **Immediate Buffer Return**: `clone()` and [release()](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/src/stream/GStreamerCamera.cpp#22-27) are performed immediately after capture. This ensures the GStreamer buffer pool (limited on RPi) never starves.
3.  **Shutdown Synchronization**: Added `camera_mutex_` and re-ordered the stop sequence to ensure [release()](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/src/stream/GStreamerCamera.cpp#22-27) doesn't race with active [read()](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/src/stream/GStreamerCamera.cpp#18-21) calls.

### CPU & Resource Optimizations
1.  **AI Downsampling (~1 FPS)**: Modified to perform AI inference only once every 30 frames (adjustable). This preserves CPU cycles for GStreamer encoding and OS tasks.
2.  **Hardware ISP Scaling**: Added `v4l2convert` to the pipeline (ISP-level scaling) to offload the `1080p -> 480p` conversion from the CPU.
3.  **Async Video Transmission**: Event recordings are transmitted in separate detached threads using a [ThreadSafeQueue](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/SubCameraApp_refactory_260311/src/util/ThreadSafeQueue.h#15-107) to prevent UI/Capture jitter.
4.  **UART Deduplication**: "Read-twice, Resend-once" strategy in the EdgeBridge prevents unintended double-movements when ACK is late.

